<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="light">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>LifeOS Atlas | Privacy Policy</title>
  <style>
    :root{--bg:#f4f5f7;--surface:#fff;--text:#15181c;--muted:#67707b;--line:#d7dde5}
    [data-theme="dark"]{--bg:#0f1318;--surface:#171c22;--text:#eef2f6;--muted:#a9b3bf;--line:#303844}
    body{margin:0;font-family:Inter,system-ui,sans-serif;background:var(--bg);color:var(--text)}
    .wrap{width:min(calc(100% - 24px),980px);margin:32px auto}
    .card{background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:24px;padding:28px}
    h1,h2{letter-spacing:-.03em} p,li{line-height:1.8;color:var(--muted)} a{color:inherit}
    .top{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap}
    .btn{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;border:none;cursor:pointer;padding:12px 16px;border-radius:999px;font-weight:800;background:transparent;border:1px solid var(--line);color:var(--text)}
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="top">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <button class="btn" id="themeToggle" type="button">Dark mode</button>
      </div>
      <p>This Privacy Policy describes how LifeOS Atlas collects, uses, protects, stores, retains, discloses, and deletes personal information. We aim to apply strong administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards appropriate to the sensitivity of the data and the nature of the service.</p>
      <h2>Information we may collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Account registration details, identity verification data, profile information, device and browser metadata, logs, support communications, transactional records, and service usage data.</li>
        <li>Information submitted through contact, onboarding, support, password recovery, account verification, community participation, or future checkout flows.</li>
        <li>Security, fraud prevention, diagnostic, and audit information reasonably necessary to protect users, the service, and legal compliance interests.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide, secure, improve, administer, troubleshoot, and personalize the service.</li>
        <li>To authenticate users, confirm accounts, process account recovery, investigate abuse, enforce policies, and support legal or regulatory obligations.</li>
        <li>To communicate service notices, operational updates, security alerts, billing-related notices, and future pricing activation notices where relevant.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Security and encryption</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We aim to use encryption in transit and appropriate encryption or equivalent safeguards at rest where suitable for the data type and system architecture.</li>
        <li>Access controls, credential protections, logging, monitoring, verification workflows, and role-based limitations may be used to reduce unauthorized access risk.</li>
        <li>No internet-based system can be guaranteed absolutely secure, but we design controls to reduce risk, detect misuse, and support incident response.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We retain data only for as long as reasonably necessary for service delivery, account administration, dispute handling, fraud prevention, legal compliance, legitimate business operations, or recordkeeping obligations.</li>
        <li>Inactive or deleted accounts may be subject to retention windows, backups, security logs, or legal hold requirements before full deletion is completed.</li>
        <li>Where deletion is requested, users may be asked to reauthenticate or verify identity before data is deleted or the account is permanently closed.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><a href="/index.html">Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script>
    (function () { const root=document.documentElement,btn=document.getElementById('themeToggle'); let mode=(window.matchMedia&&window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches)?'dark':'light'; root.setAttribute('data-theme',mode); const sync=()=>btn.textContent=mode==='dark'?'Light mode':'Dark mode'; sync(); btn.addEventListener('click',function(){mode=mode==='dark'?'light':'dark'; root.setAttribute('data-theme',mode); sync();}); })();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
